psalm.text:
[[Ps 139,1]]O LORD, you have probed me and you know me;
[[Ps 139,2]]you know when I sit and when I stand; 
you understand my thoughts from afar.
[[Ps 139,3]]My journeys and my rest you scrutinize, 
with all my ways you are familiar.

[[Ps 139,13]]Truly you have formed my inmost being; 
you knit me in my mother's womb.
[[Ps 139,14a]]I give you thanks that I am fearfully, wonderfully made;
[[Ps 139,14b]]wonderful are your works.

[[Ps 139,23]]Probe me, O God, and know my heart; 
try me, and know my thoughts;
[[Ps 139,24]]See if my way is crooked, 
and lead me in the way of old.
